Because He did not say, &#x201C;When these things begin to happen, panic.&#x201D;
He did not say, &#x201C;When these things begin to happen, never rest again.&#x201D;
He did not say, &#x201C;When these things begin to happen, it is now your job to hold the planet together.&#x201D;

He said, &#x201C;<a class="verse-link" href="https://bible.witnessweave.com/#Matthew/24/6" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="Matthew 24:6 — open in the Bible">See that you are not troubled.</a>&#x201D;
He said, &#x201C;<a class="verse-link" href="https://bible.witnessweave.com/#Matthew/6/34" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="Matthew 6:34 — open in the Bible">Do not worry about tomorrow.</a>&#x201D;
He said, &#x201C;<a class="verse-link" href="https://bible.witnessweave.com/#John/16/33" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="John 16:33 — open in the Bible">In the world you will have tribulation; but be of good cheer, I have overcome the world.</a>&#x201D;

You don&#x2019;t need another person yelling at you to &#x201C;wake up.&#x201D;
You don&#x2019;t need another voice telling you &#x201C;everything is fine.&#x201D;
You need someone to sit beside you, look you in the eye, and remind you:
